Question: Many universities require that freshman live on campus dorm during the first year of college. In your opinion, is this a good or a bad thing? Explain your opinion on this issue.
Answer:
in my opinion, it is good to require freshman to live on campus since there are lots of benefits. first, they can build their relationship with classmate and roomates. they can learn from each other, which is a good experience and skill they will use in the future. living on campus can let the freshman be familiar with the university as soon as possible.